enabled.description: Whether to enable encryption at rest. If the `encrypt_at_rest` block is not provided then this defaults to `false`. Enabling encryption on new domains requires `elasticsearch_version` 5.1 or greater.

kmsKeyId.description: KMS key ARN to encrypt the Elasticsearch domain with. If not specified then it defaults to using the `aws/es` service KMS key. Note that KMS will accept a KMS key ID but will return the key ARN. To prevent the provider detecting unwanted changes, use the key ARN instead.
